! Minimal FRR startup-config for the inter-cluster router.
!
! Rendered by boxman via Jinja2 before `containerlab deploy`. boxman's
! env() / env_required() helpers are available.
!
! This file lands at /etc/frr/frr.conf inside the router container. The
! kernel-side address assignments and IP forwarding sysctl are applied
! by the topology's `exec:` block — they are duplicated here as FRR
! interface stanzas so the FRR config self-documents the routing setup
! and so `vtysh -c 'show ip route'` produces meaningful output.
!
frr defaults traditional
hostname {{ env("BOXMAN_FRR_HOSTNAME", default="router-frr") }}
log syslog informational
service integrated-vtysh-config
!
ip forwarding
!
interface eth1
 description to-cluster-1-via-bx_inter_a
 ip address 10.10.1.1/24
!
interface eth2
 description to-cluster-2-via-bx_inter_b
 ip address 10.10.2.1/24
!
! Both transit subnets are directly connected to the router; no static
! routes or routing protocols are needed for the demo. Add `router bgp`
! / `router ospf` blocks here to extend the example.
!
end
